org.cpsolver.coursett.neighbourhoods

Class RoomSwap

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cpsolver.ifs.algorithms.neighbourhoods.RandomSwapMove<Lecture,Placement>
      • org.cpsolver.coursett.neighbourhoods.RoomSwap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HillClimberSelection, NeighbourSelection<Lecture,Placement>

    public class RoomSwap
extends RandomSwapMove<Lecture,Placement>
    Try to assign a class with a new room. A class is selected randomly, a different room is randomly selected for the class -- the class is assigned into the new room. If the room is used or there is some other conflict, it tries to resolve these conflicts by assigning conflicting classes to other rooms as well.
    Version:
    IFS 1.3 (Iterative Forward Search)
